Went in and waited in line to purchase a pound of cookies. Girl in front was busy and asked for help. Another shows up and asked what I needed. I told her a pound of cookies. She asked if she could select and I told her no. I will tell her what variety I want. She asked the next individual in line what he needed and apparently it was just bread. She proceeded to get his bread before my cookies. Told me it would only take her a minute. I didn’t come into your bakery and wait in line for you to decide to take care of the guy behind me first. I don’t care if it was just bread. It’s not his turn! I’m not sure I care to entertain what her problem is. I could only guess,  but if I go back in there and I receive anything close to poor customer service again. I will call it out and address it on the spot.

I grew up with this place. As a very young boy we would pick up our loaves of bread for our traditional Italian Sunday dinner. Times have changed, the Sunday dinners no longer take place the area has also dramatically changed from the old Italian neighborhood to a gentrified place. One thing that hasn't changed much and that's D'Amato's. I have to admit I don't frequent nearly as much as I once did but my girlfriend told me she had never had a Cannoli the other day. WTF? I almost broke up with her on the spot but I didn't instead I brought to the place that as far as I'm concerned put the 'C' in Cannoli. D'Amato's has awesome Cannoli great Bakery pizza some people call it Sicilian style pizza which if you're not familiar with it, it's kind of like Focaccia bread. Their loaves of bread are second to none! I love this place it brings me back to the happiest times in my life.
